      <problem id="prob-00005">
      <para id="para-00022">The data set NHL19 (found at ESPN.com) gives the results of the 2018-2019 National Hockey League season. The columns are team, wins (W), losses (L), overtime losses (OTL), total points (PTS), goals scored by the team (GF), goals scored against the team (GA), and goal differential (the difference in GF and GA). Use Google Sheets to create a scatter plot for GF vs. GA.</para>
      <note class="check-point" id="note-00006">
      <para id="para-00023">When we talk about plotting one set versus another, the first is the response and the second is explanatory.</para>
      </note>
      </problem>
      <solution id="sol-00005">
